My Meme

The new meme is just Verne the turtle from over the hedge, it’s just my reaction when i forget about assignments

Here is my meme

library(magick)

#turtle image from read url
turtle <- image_read("https://streamsentials.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/HUH-PNG.png")

#background and annotation for meme
background <- image_blank(width = 300, height = 300, color = "black")%>%
  image_annotate(text = "when you have an assignment due", gravity = "north", size = 18, color = "green")%>%
  image_annotate(text = "in 2 hours", gravity = "south", size = 50, color = "green")

#resize of turtle meme  
resize_turtle <- image_resize(turtle, "300x300")

#appending the background and turtle meme
new_meme <- image_append(c(background, resize_turtle))

#create png image of new meme
image_write(new_meme, "my_meme.png")

My Animated GIF

The animation gif i made was just different poses of Verne and a close up meme of him which I thought was funny

Here is my animation

library(magick)

#reading and assigning 4 turtle pictures from 4 different urls
turtle_1 <- image_read("https://w7.pngwing.com/pngs/608/120/png-transparent-over-the-hedge-turtle-character-illustration-over-the-hedge-hammy-turtle-film-dreamworks-animation-turtle-animals-actor-toy.png")

turtle_2 <- image_read("https://e7.pngegg.com/pngimages/776/183/png-clipart-over-the-hedge-hammy-goes-nuts-youtube-animated-film-others-terrestrial-animal-desktop-wallpaper.png")

turtle_3 <- image_read("https://e7.pngegg.com/pngimages/516/744/png-clipart-hammy-dreamworks-animation-film-graphy-turtle-animals-photography.png")

turtle_4 <- image_read("https://streamsentials.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/HUH-PNG.png")

#storing 4 turtle images to turtle_images
turtle_images <- c(turtle_1, turtle_2, turtle_3, turtle_4)

#scaling the images to 300x300
turtle_images <- image_scale(turtle_images, "300x300")

#animating the 4 turtle images into a gif of 1 frame per second
turtle_gif <- image_animate(image_scale(turtle_images, "300x300"), fps = 1, dispose = "previous")

#creating gif of the 4 turtle images animated
image_write(turtle_gif, "my_animation.gif")
